      out.write("<div style=\"width:1400px;overflow-x:auto;margin:25px 0 0 0;\">\r\n  <div class=\"appSetupStepContent clearfix\" style=\"margin:0 0 0 180px;width:850px;float:left;\">\r\n    <img src=\"/integration/dropbox/icons/dropbox-logo.png\" style=\"float:left;margin:25px;\" />\r\n    <div style=\"float:left;\">\r\n      <h1 style=\"font-size:25px;float:left;margin:25px 0 0 25px;\">");
      out.print(bundle.getString("ragicDocFullname"));
      out.write("</h1>\r\n      <a href=\"/");
      out.print(rp.getApname());
      out.write("/apps/dropbox/index\">\r\n        <div class=\"thebuttonBlue\" style=\"margin:18px 0 0 50px;clear:both;float:right;\">Link another folder</div>\r\n      </a>\r\n      <p style=\"float:left;clear:left;margin:12px 0 0 25px;color:#aaa;\">");
      out.print(bundle.getString("ragicDocSlogan"));
      out.write("</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"location\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Location of your documents</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>Access your first document management app from the \"Documents\" tab on the top.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/tab.png\" />\r\n      <p>This will take you to your listing page, where all your synced documents are listed.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/list_hover_TPS.png\" />\r\n      <p>Clicking on any of the listed entries will take you to the form page, where you can configure sharing and add detailed information about your documents.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_tps.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"share\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Sharing documents</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>If you have set up your document management application in Ragic for <b>Internal</b> usage, you can <a href=\"#adduser\">add users</a> to share documents with them.</p>\r\n      <p>If you have set your application for <b>External</b> usage, you can share documents by sending the URL on your address bar after making sure that others you are sharing have the correct <a href=\"#access\">access rights</a>.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("    <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/share.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"search\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Search / full text search</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>To search for text within your documents in Ragic, begin typing on the top search bar, which will display results simultaneously.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/search_top.png\" />\r\n      <p>You can also use text to quickly filter documents by their document name. To do so, click on the little arrow next to the field <b>File Name</b>, and select \"Filter by Text\"</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/search_filtertext.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/search_filtertextresult.png\" />\r\n      <p>You can also use filters to search as well. In the example below, we are selecting a filter from the dropdown menu to display results from a single folder.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/search_filterdropdown.png\" />\r\n      <p>A more fine-tuned search can done through the left sidebar search tool.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/search_filterleft.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"add\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Adding documents</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>To add a new document from Ragic to sync with your Dropbox storage, click on the <b>+New</b> button from the top of your sheet. This will take you to an empty form.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/new1.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/new2.png\" />\r\n      <p>Upload your document, select the users and user groups to share, and Ragic will sync the uploaded document with Dropbox after saving.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"update\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Updating documents</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>Update your document through Ragic to keep all the data such as the history and comments about this document. The changes you have made to the document will also sync with Dropbox. Just upload the new document by clicking the clipboard icon in the entry about this document. </p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/update1.png\" />\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/update2.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"adduser\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Adding new users</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>Add users from your <b>Account Setup</b>, located under your <b>Getting Started</b> tab.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/user_account_setup.png\" />\r\n      <p>Click on the <b>+New</b> button to add a new user.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/user_list.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/user_form.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"comment\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Commenting</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>You can comment on the forms that contain detailed data about your uploaded documents from the bottom-right side of the form page to have conversations. Just click on <b>Comments</b>, and the comment box will pop up.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/comment1.png\" />\r\n      <p>Write your comment and attach a file if you would like to. It is also possible to attach a file without writing additional comments.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/comment2.png\" />\r\n      <p>The user assigned as the owner of this document as well as other users that are sharing this document will be notified, and will be able to see your comment from the bottom-right corner.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/comment3.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"folder\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Change folder</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>You can change which folder your document belongs to inside Dropbox through Ragic. Just edit the field <b>Folder</b> in the entry about this document, and it will sync with Dropbox.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_tps.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/folder.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"delete\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Deleting documents</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>To delete document from Ragic, you can delete the entry that contains the document. Click on the <b>Tools</b> button, and the option <b>Delete Entry</b>.\r\n        <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/delete_form.png\" />\r\n");
      out.write("      <p>To delete multiple entries, you can go to your listing page where all your documents are listed, and click <b>Delete Filtered</b> under the <b>Tools</b> button. This will delete the filtered results. If you haven't done any filtering, then all your documents under this sheet will be deleted.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/delete_list.png\" />\r\n      <p>Deleting entries from Ragic will not delete your files from Dropbox, but if you delete documents from Dropbox, they will be deleted in Ragic.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"design\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Changing form design</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>You can change the design of your form that contains detailed data about your uploaded documents. Just click on <b>Change Design</b> button on your form page to go to the <b>Design Mode</b>.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_changedesign.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/design.png\" />\r\n      <p>You can add new fields by beginning to type on an empty cell, and configure the field type.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/design_newfield.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/design_fieldtype.png\" />\r\n      <p>Don't forget to save your changes when exiting the design mode.</p>\r\n      <p>There are many ways to edit the design of forms in Ragic, which is explained in detail in our <a href=\"https://www.ragic.com/intl/en/doc\">developer guide</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"access\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Change access rights</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>The <b>Access Rights</b> to your document management sheet determines the users and user groups that can see the shared document and other stored data on your sheet. You can change the access right settings on your sheet by going to the <b>Design Mode</b>. You will find the <b>Access Rights</b> tab under <b>Form Settings</b>.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_changedesign.png\" />\r\n      <p>All of the user groups in your account will be listed here, as well as an additional group <b>Everyone</b>, which represents everyone, including the users who haven't logged in, or individuals who are not a user in your account.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("      <p>You can set the access rights for every group of users listed here. The access privileges that are being set is specified on the configuration interface. If a user is in multiple groups, they will access the form with the group that grants them the most privilege.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/access1.png\" />\r\n      <p>You can also add custom groups by clicking on \"Add User Group\", under the list of your user groups.</p>\r\n      <p>Remember to save the form design after you change the access right setting. You do not need to set this to both listing page and form page, the access right is applied to all pages of a sheet.</p>\r\n      <p>You can fine-tune the shared user groups within the form you are filling for each document you are sharing. Just select which user groups can see this form in addition to the user groups you have set for your sheet.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/access2.png\" />\r\n      <p>If a user still cannot see the data after you grant them the privilege, ask them to log out and log back in to refresh their access right settings.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"assign\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Assign an entry</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>You can assign your documents to a certain user a user group through the <b>Owner</b>, <b>Shared User</b>, or <b>Shared Group</b> fields, which gives that user the access right to that document.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_tps.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/assign.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <a name=\"approval\"></a>\r\n    <h2>Configuring approval</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"appSetupDocSection\">\r\n      <p>You may configure the <b>Approval</b> process for your document management sheet in Ragic. Configure the approval flow of your document management forms under your sheet by going to the <b>Design Mode</b>.</p>\r\n      <p>Click on the <b>Change Design</b> button on any of your forms to access the <b>Design Mode</b>.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/form_changedesign.png\" />\r\n      <p>You will see a checkbox in the lower-right hand corner.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval0.png\" />\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval1.png\" />\r\n      <p>You can add as many approval steps as you would like to from the configuration box. Set the <b>Approver Title</b> and <b>Name</b> for each approval step. You may set the Approver under Name to be a certain person from your <b>Users</b>, or to be selected later when starting the approval, from one of your <b>User Groups</b>.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval2.png\" />\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval3.png\" />\r\n      <p>After finishing setting up the approval steps, don't forget to <b>Save</b> the changes you have made.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval4.png\" />\r\n      <p>The approval steps you have set for the form will show up in every entry. Clicking the <b>Start Approval</b> button will begin the approval process.</p>\r\n      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval5.png\" />\r\n      <p>Doing so will display the <b>Approval status</b> as \"Pending approval\". The selected user or users in the user group will be notified for an <b>Approval Request</b>. The Approval Status will update as the sheet is approved. You can find the approval box in the lower-right side of your form page.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("      <img src=\"/intl/common/img/dropboxkb/approval6.png\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"appHomeSidebar\">\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#location\"><li>Location of documents</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#share\"><li>Sharing documents</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#search\"><li>Search / full text search</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#add\"><li>Adding documents</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#update\"><li>Updating documents</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#adduser\"><li>Adding users</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#comment\"><li>Commenting</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#folder\"><li>Change folder</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#delete\"><li>Deleting documents</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#design\"><li>Changing form design</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#access\"><li>Change access rights</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#assign\"><li>Assign an entry</li></a>\r\n        <a href=\"manage#approval\"><li>Approval</li></a>\r\n      </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>");
